    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Process, typically taking place according to customary or legal principle, by which one person, or sometimes multiple people or a state, succeeds another in the occupation or possession of a throne, land, or estate. The act or fact of succession typically binds the successor legally to the rights and liabilities of the predecessor.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
